WEBVTT

00:00:15.490 --> 00:00:16.400
All right.

00:00:16.540 --> 00:00:21.390
Should we get started?

00:00:21.480 --> 00:00:22.690
My name is Max Muller.

00:00:22.750 --> 00:00:26.040
I'm the director of the iTunes
Store Content Engineering Group.

00:00:26.130 --> 00:00:28.700
It's my group's responsibility
for building the infrastructure

00:00:28.700 --> 00:00:32.790
for handling all things content,
from content acquisition all the

00:00:32.880 --> 00:00:36.560
way through to content delivery
and everything in between.

00:00:36.670 --> 00:00:39.480
To set the stage for this session,
we're going to be looking at

00:00:39.480 --> 00:00:42.770
the process of taking a final,
finished application and

00:00:42.770 --> 00:00:44.640
publishing it to the App Store.

00:00:44.730 --> 00:00:47.680
But before we start to talk
about where we're going,

00:00:47.730 --> 00:00:50.020
let's first look at where we've been.

00:00:50.900 --> 00:00:55.550
April 2003,
Apple launched the iTunes Music Store,

00:00:55.690 --> 00:01:00.200
a revolutionary online music store
featuring over 200,000 tracks,

00:01:00.340 --> 00:01:03.940
free 30-second previews,
simple one-click purchase and download,

00:01:03.940 --> 00:01:07.430
and worry-free transfer to iPod.

00:01:07.930 --> 00:01:10.710
Fast forward five years,
as one of the original

00:01:10.710 --> 00:01:12.950
iTunes Store engineers,
I can tell you,

00:01:12.990 --> 00:01:15.790
it's been an action-packed five years.

00:01:16.900 --> 00:01:20.180
Today, the iTunes Store operates
in 22 countries.

00:01:20.330 --> 00:01:25.660
It features movies, TV shows,
music videos, audiobooks, podcasts,

00:01:25.810 --> 00:01:27.320
and iPod games.

00:01:27.520 --> 00:01:30.530
This past quarter,
the iTunes Store reached a major

00:01:30.640 --> 00:01:34.710
milestone and is now the largest
retailer of music in the world.

00:01:36.180 --> 00:01:40.820
September 2007, Apple launched the
iTunes Wi-Fi Music Store.

00:01:40.850 --> 00:01:45.840
Browse, search, preview, purchase,
and download right on

00:01:45.840 --> 00:01:48.570
your iPhone or iPod touch.

00:01:49.700 --> 00:01:52.670
and this past January,
Apple released the iTunes

00:01:52.790 --> 00:01:56.480
Store for Apple TV,
bringing simple HD movie rental

00:01:56.900 --> 00:01:59.550
right to your widescreen television.

00:01:59.780 --> 00:02:03.560
Apple has accumulated five
years of experience in hosting,

00:02:03.620 --> 00:02:07.760
distributing,
and managing online digital content.

00:02:08.020 --> 00:02:11.220
and we're building on that
infrastructure now to deliver the

00:02:11.220 --> 00:02:15.960
App Store to you and all your friends
and all your friends' friends.

00:02:16.920 --> 00:02:22.140
The App Store is really a revolution
in online software distribution.

00:02:22.170 --> 00:02:25.940
Apple is handling all the
infrastructure for the App Store by

00:02:25.940 --> 00:02:29.690
leveraging everything that
we've built for the iTunes Store.

00:02:30.050 --> 00:02:34.380
on the hosting side,
we host over 6 million unique songs.

00:02:34.430 --> 00:02:38.800
And we're adding a new song to the
catalog on average every two seconds.

00:02:38.840 --> 00:02:42.070
On the distribution front,
the iTunes Store operates

00:02:42.070 --> 00:02:43.340
in 22 countries.

00:02:43.390 --> 00:02:46.620
And just for you,
adding 40 more countries,

00:02:46.670 --> 00:02:49.360
bringing the total to 62
countries that you will be able to

00:02:49.360 --> 00:02:52.140
distribute your applications into.

00:02:52.260 --> 00:02:55.960
On the payment processing front,
we have over 50 million

00:02:55.960 --> 00:03:01.540
accounts in the iTunes Store,
and we've sold over 4 billion songs.

00:03:01.650 --> 00:03:05.390
Specific to the App Store,
Apple is bringing a seamless

00:03:05.440 --> 00:03:09.190
download and installation experience,
along with an automatic,

00:03:09.370 --> 00:03:12.140
unified software update system.

00:03:12.290 --> 00:03:16.580
And starting in early July,

00:03:16.940 --> 00:03:20.540
Apple is putting the App Store front
and center on every iPhone

00:03:20.780 --> 00:03:23.870
and every iPod touch we ship,
as well as integrating the

00:03:23.870 --> 00:03:26.200
App Store directly into iTunes.

00:03:26.280 --> 00:03:29.510
So in your search for Foo,
not only are you going

00:03:29.510 --> 00:03:32.200
to find Foo Fighters,
but you're also going to

00:03:32.200 --> 00:03:33.980
find FooBar by Acme Inc.

00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:36.660
So what does this mean to you?

00:03:36.700 --> 00:03:39.040
This means you get to
focus on the fun part,

00:03:39.110 --> 00:03:41.080
writing great applications.

00:03:41.080 --> 00:03:42.860
Because you don't have to
worry about credit card,

00:03:42.900 --> 00:03:45.200
marketing, or hosting fees.

00:03:45.250 --> 00:03:48.210
For commercial distribution,
70% of the proceeds are

00:03:48.450 --> 00:03:50.900
going to go straight to you,
the developer.

00:03:50.900 --> 00:03:53.020
And free apps are, well,

00:03:53.100 --> 00:03:54.540
free.

00:03:54.620 --> 00:03:56.840
So at this point,
this is what Apple's bringing

00:03:56.840 --> 00:03:58.800
to the table for the App Store.

00:03:58.820 --> 00:04:02.340
And now we need a bunch of great
software engineers to write a

00:04:02.350 --> 00:04:05.960
bunch of great software and get it
published up onto the App Store.

00:04:07.030 --> 00:04:10.140
So let's imagine I'm a great
software developer and I've written

00:04:10.140 --> 00:04:13.880
an amazing application called
Touch Fighter and I've gotten

00:04:13.880 --> 00:04:16.540
this published up on the App Store.

00:04:16.620 --> 00:04:19.780
Let's first start by looking at what
the customer experience of interacting

00:04:19.840 --> 00:04:25.010
with Touch Fighter is going to be on
the App Store as well as within iTunes.

00:04:26.890 --> 00:04:29.780
So this is what Touch Fighter is
going to look like in a list view.

00:04:29.920 --> 00:04:33.760
Someone would have gotten to this
either by browsing or via search.

00:04:33.800 --> 00:04:37.220
Notice we're displaying the icon,
the company name,

00:04:37.220 --> 00:04:40.500
and the application name,
as well as the average

00:04:40.500 --> 00:04:43.880
user rating from our kind,
gentle users.

00:04:46.220 --> 00:04:50.300
and this is what a product page for
Touch Fighter is going to look like.

00:04:50.350 --> 00:04:54.940
Notice at this point we've added a
description as well as a screenshot.

00:04:54.990 --> 00:04:57.750
A customer at this point with one
click would be able to purchase

00:04:57.990 --> 00:05:01.580
and download the app and play
Touch Fighter on their phone.

00:05:03.300 --> 00:05:06.100
and this is what Touch Fighter is
going to look like in iTunes.

00:05:06.150 --> 00:05:08.740
Notice it's the same information
but would now display it

00:05:09.130 --> 00:05:12.100
in a full rich iTunes page.

00:05:12.150 --> 00:05:15.180
With one click at this point,
the customer could purchase and download

00:05:15.180 --> 00:05:17.240
Touch Fighter to their computer.

00:05:17.300 --> 00:05:19.910
The next time they plug in their phone,
they could choose to sync the app over

00:05:20.330 --> 00:05:22.590
and play Touch Fighter on their phone.

00:05:23.170 --> 00:05:27.620
So this is what the customer experience
is with interacting with Touch Fighter on

00:05:27.620 --> 00:05:30.700
the App Store as well as with an iTunes.

00:05:30.790 --> 00:05:32.880
So now let's talk about you.

00:05:33.170 --> 00:05:35.850
How are you going to be able to
publish your application to the

00:05:36.010 --> 00:05:39.810
App Store so that it can look
even better than Touch Fighter?

00:05:40.500 --> 00:05:42.040
Well, you're in luck.

00:05:42.110 --> 00:05:46.550
Publishing your app to the App Store is
a simple five-step process.

00:05:46.820 --> 00:05:51.940
The first step is to set up
an account in iTunes Connect.

00:05:52.030 --> 00:05:56.340
iTunes Connect is your online web
portal for managing your content and

00:05:56.340 --> 00:05:59.140
your presence within the App Store.

00:05:59.220 --> 00:06:01.780
iTunes Connect is used
by our music labels,

00:06:01.870 --> 00:06:04.580
our TV studios,
our post-production houses,

00:06:04.580 --> 00:06:06.070
and our movie studios.

00:06:06.220 --> 00:06:10.430
If you can buy and download a piece
of content within the iTunes Store,

00:06:10.500 --> 00:06:14.190
someone from that company has
an account in iTunes Connect.

00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:18.990
The prerequisite to set up an account
for App Store publishing is that

00:06:19.050 --> 00:06:23.900
you must be a standard or enterprise
member of the iPhone developer program.

00:06:23.980 --> 00:06:26.290
If you are currently only
developing and running your

00:06:26.290 --> 00:06:28.760
application within the simulator,
then grasshopper,

00:06:28.880 --> 00:06:32.110
you are not ready to publish
an app to the App Store.

00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:36.840
The first time you access
the iTunes Connect,

00:06:36.840 --> 00:06:40.190
you're going to want to have your
administrator log in to the iPhone

00:06:40.540 --> 00:06:42.580
developer or program portal.

00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:47.700
From there, they should click on
the distribution link.

00:06:47.780 --> 00:06:50.670
This will talk you through everything
you need to know about setting up

00:06:50.670 --> 00:06:54.820
a distribution signing identity,
a distribution provisioning profile,

00:06:54.890 --> 00:06:58.100
and it will also have a
link to iTunes Connect.

00:06:58.440 --> 00:07:01.500
Once you log into iTunes Connect,
you'll end up here.

00:07:01.570 --> 00:07:03.230
This is the home screen.

00:07:03.350 --> 00:07:08.400
For App Store users,
there are four modules: Contracts,

00:07:08.490 --> 00:07:13.530
Financial Reports, Manage Users,
and Manager Content.

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:16.300
Later on in the presentation,
we'll go into more detail about

00:07:16.300 --> 00:07:17.900
all four of these modules.

00:07:17.970 --> 00:07:21.040
But for now,
we're done with the first step.

00:07:21.090 --> 00:07:23.360
We have an account.

00:07:23.600 --> 00:07:27.480
Next up, we're going to add a new app.

00:07:27.690 --> 00:07:30.320
To do that,
we log into iTunes Connect and

00:07:30.320 --> 00:07:32.520
click "Manage Your Content."

00:07:33.900 --> 00:07:37.510
If this is your first time logging
into the content management module,

00:07:37.520 --> 00:07:42.440
I highly suggest you download the
user guide linked off the middle part.

00:07:42.560 --> 00:07:47.220
The user guide contains detailed
instructions as well as examples

00:07:47.730 --> 00:07:50.610
for everything that you will need to
provide to us when you submit your

00:07:50.640 --> 00:07:52.030
application through the App Store.

00:07:52.760 --> 00:07:55.140
All of your applications
that you previously submitted

00:07:55.430 --> 00:07:56.560
would be listed here.

00:07:56.560 --> 00:08:00.010
You'll be coming back into this
page to make edits to any of your

00:08:00.010 --> 00:08:03.280
metadata that you provided to us,
as well as to provide a new

00:08:03.290 --> 00:08:05.250
binary for the update process.

00:08:05.300 --> 00:08:08.170
Now, I've already read the user guide,
so I'm going to click on

00:08:08.170 --> 00:08:10.760
the upper left-hand button
to add a new application.

00:08:13.230 --> 00:08:16.610
The first time you add a new app,
we are going to ask you for

00:08:16.700 --> 00:08:18.740
two pieces of information.

00:08:18.910 --> 00:08:22.040
The first is your primary
or default language.

00:08:22.200 --> 00:08:25.140
This will come into play when we
start to talk about how you localize

00:08:25.140 --> 00:08:27.140
your pages within the App Store.

00:08:27.290 --> 00:08:29.820
But for now,
what we want to know from you is what

00:08:29.820 --> 00:08:34.600
language are you filling out all of
the metadata about your application in?

00:08:34.790 --> 00:08:37.160
The second is your company name.

00:08:37.260 --> 00:08:39.740
This is your brand within iTunes.

00:08:39.830 --> 00:08:42.900
Every application that you
submit to the App Store will be

00:08:42.900 --> 00:08:44.920
listed under this company name.

00:08:45.090 --> 00:08:47.660
Now, the other thing to point out about
these two pieces of information

00:08:47.660 --> 00:08:50.350
is that right now we don't
have any facility to edit them,

00:08:50.380 --> 00:08:54.090
so you want to make sure you
get them right the first time.

00:08:55.750 --> 00:08:58.760
Next up,
we're going to enter the details or

00:08:58.760 --> 00:09:01.580
the metadata about our application.

00:09:03.020 --> 00:09:06.340
The first question we're going to
ask you is about export compliance.

00:09:06.520 --> 00:09:09.720
The iTunes Store servers are
located within the United States,

00:09:09.750 --> 00:09:12.740
and as such,
any time you move a binary to us,

00:09:12.740 --> 00:09:15.330
we are going to ask you three
questions about your use of encryption.

00:09:15.340 --> 00:09:18.630
The first is,
does your product contain encryption?

00:09:18.690 --> 00:09:22.860
The second, is encryption used for
authentication purposes only?

00:09:22.860 --> 00:09:25.490
And the third,
is encryption used for the protection of

00:09:25.560 --> 00:09:27.720
data or information security purposes?

00:09:27.750 --> 00:09:32.850
If you answer yes to the third question,
we are going to require that you upload

00:09:32.850 --> 00:09:35.260
a PDF copy of your CCATS file to us.

00:09:35.260 --> 00:09:38.920
If you don't know what a CCATS file is,
and you think you might need one,

00:09:38.920 --> 00:09:40.640
I'm going to refer you to the U.S.

00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:42.860
Department of
Commerce Commercial Encryption

00:09:42.910 --> 00:09:46.040
Export Control's website for
further fascinating reading.

00:09:50.800 --> 00:09:54.080
Next up is to provide the
details about your application.

00:09:54.160 --> 00:09:57.960
This is your application name,
description, categories,

00:09:58.030 --> 00:10:01.500
copyright and version information,
as well as an application

00:10:01.500 --> 00:10:02.790
and support URL.

00:10:03.330 --> 00:10:06.900
and finally a support email and an
end user license agreement if you

00:10:06.900 --> 00:10:09.600
have one as well as a SKU number.

00:10:09.680 --> 00:10:11.720
Later on in the presentation
we'll go into more detail

00:10:12.020 --> 00:10:16.140
about all of these fields,
but for now the only thing I'd like

00:10:16.140 --> 00:10:21.160
to point out is that your SKU number
is not on a customer visible field.

00:10:21.250 --> 00:10:24.340
It's only used for you for
within your financial reports.

00:10:24.450 --> 00:10:29.820
Once you've submitted a SKU number to us,
you cannot change your SKU number.

00:10:31.510 --> 00:10:33.960
Next up are your supported devices.

00:10:34.120 --> 00:10:38.900
The App Store differentiates
applications between two sets of devices.

00:10:38.950 --> 00:10:42.640
An application that works on
the iPhone and the iPod touch

00:10:43.110 --> 00:10:45.560
and an iPhone only application.

00:10:45.670 --> 00:10:48.860
If, for instance,
your application requires the use

00:10:48.860 --> 00:10:52.870
of the camera or the microphone,
you are going to want to indicate

00:10:52.870 --> 00:10:56.410
your application as being
an iPhone only application.

00:10:56.620 --> 00:11:00.130
It should be noted that iPhone
only applications will be filtered

00:11:00.130 --> 00:11:04.490
out and not visible within the
App Store on the iPod touch.

00:11:06.070 --> 00:11:09.130
Optionally, if you have categorized
your application as a game,

00:11:09.130 --> 00:11:14.080
we are going to ask you to provide
the frequency or intensity level

00:11:14.590 --> 00:11:16.180
of the following game advisories.

00:11:16.180 --> 00:11:20.500
Based on these game advisories,
we'll determine the rating of

00:11:20.500 --> 00:11:22.880
your game within the App Store.

00:11:23.520 --> 00:11:31.590
The App Store has four age-based ratings,
4+, 9+, 12+, and 17+. I should

00:11:31.590 --> 00:11:36.100
point out that iTunes will offer
parental advisory controls to limit

00:11:36.100 --> 00:11:38.570
access to games of certain ratings.

00:11:42.050 --> 00:11:44.130
At that point,
we've provided all the metadata

00:11:44.130 --> 00:11:47.500
we need to about our application.

00:11:47.510 --> 00:11:50.310
Next up is the actual assets.

00:11:51.210 --> 00:11:54.340
The first and most important
asset is obviously your binary.

00:11:54.390 --> 00:11:56.770
There are a few things that you
need to ensure about your binary

00:11:56.780 --> 00:11:58.440
before you upload it to us.

00:11:58.940 --> 00:12:04.020
The first is that you have
included a 57 by 57 PNG icon.

00:12:04.480 --> 00:12:08.360
Note the rounded corners as well as
shine are automatically applied by

00:12:08.360 --> 00:12:10.880
both the App Store and the phone.

00:12:11.320 --> 00:12:15.250
If you've chosen to pre-render your icon,
the App Store will respect the

00:12:15.250 --> 00:12:19.500
UI pre-rendered icon key if you
set it in your Xcode project.

00:12:21.020 --> 00:12:22.860
Next up is your app ID.

00:12:22.900 --> 00:12:26.640
You register your app ID within
the iPhone developer portal.

00:12:26.680 --> 00:12:29.710
You'll use that app ID to create
a distribution provisioning

00:12:29.710 --> 00:12:32.100
profile for your application.

00:12:32.130 --> 00:12:35.500
You should set up a separate
distribution provisioning profile

00:12:35.500 --> 00:12:39.300
for each unique application that
you plan to submit to the App Store.

00:12:41.880 --> 00:12:44.680
Last is to actually
build your application.

00:12:44.730 --> 00:12:48.170
Little bit different than building
it for your development or testing.

00:12:48.290 --> 00:12:51.240
So in Xcode, you're gonna set your
active SDK to device.

00:12:51.540 --> 00:12:54.280
You're gonna set your active
configuration to release.

00:12:54.340 --> 00:12:56.260
You're gonna set your code
signing identity to be

00:12:56.260 --> 00:12:57.980
your distribution identity.

00:12:58.020 --> 00:13:01.120
This is not the same as
your development identity.

00:13:01.160 --> 00:13:04.490
And last, you're gonna set your code
signing provisioning profile to

00:13:04.490 --> 00:13:08.670
be the distribution provisioning
profile for that application.

00:13:09.250 --> 00:13:12.010
After your application has
been built in the Finder,

00:13:12.020 --> 00:13:14.890
you're going to compress
it to a zip archive.

00:13:15.130 --> 00:13:21.330
This zip archive is what you will
then be uploading to the App Store.

00:13:23.320 --> 00:13:27.750
So what about if you get your zip
together and it's 500 megabytes?

00:13:27.870 --> 00:13:31.040
Turns out the web experience for
uploading a 500 megabyte file is

00:13:31.040 --> 00:13:34.010
what we would call less than ideal.

00:13:35.370 --> 00:13:38.760
How we solve this problem for
our music and video partners is

00:13:38.760 --> 00:13:42.290
we actually provide software to
them that they then use to upload

00:13:42.290 --> 00:13:44.620
terabytes of content to us every week.

00:13:44.740 --> 00:13:47.900
So we've taken that same
core infrastructure and we

00:13:47.930 --> 00:13:51.920
built a nice Cocoa app called
Application Loader just for you.

00:13:51.940 --> 00:13:54.770
With Application Loader,
you log in with your

00:13:54.770 --> 00:13:56.520
iTunes Connect account.

00:13:56.520 --> 00:13:59.700
Once logged in,
you will see a listing of all of the

00:13:59.700 --> 00:14:04.900
applications that you have submitted to
us that are awaiting a binary upload.

00:14:06.560 --> 00:14:09.790
selecting one of those applications,
you can then select a zip

00:14:09.790 --> 00:14:12.700
file and hit transfer,
at which point you can watch

00:14:12.760 --> 00:14:16.500
the progress as your binary
will move up to our servers.

00:14:16.500 --> 00:14:19.560
If for whatever reason your
transfer should get interrupted,

00:14:19.560 --> 00:14:21.730
you can just hit resume
and pick it right up,

00:14:21.740 --> 00:14:24.500
pick it right back up right where it was.

00:14:24.530 --> 00:14:28.460
Once the application has
successfully moved to our servers,

00:14:28.460 --> 00:14:33.500
you'll get a nice confirmation dialogue
that you'll know that you're done.

00:14:33.720 --> 00:14:37.980
Now, we are going to require the
use of Application Loader.

00:14:43.610 --> 00:14:47.050
We're going to require the use
of Application Loader if your zip

00:14:47.130 --> 00:14:49.640
archive is over 200 megabytes.

00:14:49.690 --> 00:14:53.600
However, anyone can elect to use
Application Loader if you are on a

00:14:53.600 --> 00:14:56.200
slow or spotty internet connection.

00:14:56.450 --> 00:14:59.590
and the last thing to point out is
that we do have a hard limit of two

00:14:59.590 --> 00:15:03.750
gigabytes where we will not accept any
archive that is over two gigabytes.

00:15:03.940 --> 00:15:06.830
Now, since we are still
within the beta program,

00:15:06.860 --> 00:15:08.440
at this point,
we don't want you to upload

00:15:08.440 --> 00:15:10.440
a binary to us just yet.

00:15:10.510 --> 00:15:15.050
For today,
we're looking at you setting up

00:15:15.150 --> 00:15:18.600
all your metadata within iTunes
Connect and we'll notify you at a

00:15:18.610 --> 00:15:22.380
later point when we're ready for
